A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 52-7-8.3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 operation of watercraft, identification, and operation by minors, so as to provide for boat
3 liveries and education courses; to provide for a penalty; to provide for definitions; to provide
4 for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Code Section 52-7-8.3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to operation of
8 watercraft, identification, and operation by minors, is amended by revising subsection (g) as
9 follows:
10 "(g)(1) As used in this subsection, the term: No person shall rent, lease, or let for hire any
11 vessel ten horsepower or more to any person under 16 years of age. On and after July 1,
12 2014, a person 16 years of age or older may rent or lease any vessel ten horsepower or
13 more if such person has completed a boating education course approved by the
14 department. This subsection shall not apply to any person licensed by the United States
15 Coast Guard as a master of a vessel or a nonresident who has in his or her possession
16 proof that he or she has completed a National Association of State Boating Law
