17 Administrators approved boater education course or equivalency examination from
18 another state.
19 (A) 'Boat livery' means a business which holds any vessel for renting, leasing, or
20 chartering.
21 (B) 'Course' means a rental education course as provided for in paragraph (3) of this
22 subsection.
23 (C) 'Person' means an individual, partnership, firm, corporation, association, or other
24 legal entity.
25 (2) A boat livery may not rent, lease, or let for hire any vessel ten horsepower or more
26 to any person under 16 years of age. A boat livery may rent, lease, or let for hire a vessel
27 ten horsepower or more to a person 16 years of age or older if such person, and one
28 additional person 16 years of age or older who will be present on such vessel, has
29 completed a rental education course approved by the department's Law Enforcement
30 Division and if all persons 16 years of age or older who intend to operate such vessel
31 have also completed a course.
32 (3) Rental education courses provided by boat liveries pursuant to paragraph (2) of this
33 subsection must be approved by the department's Law Enforcement Division and must
34 result in the issuance of a rental education certificate by such division upon successful
35 completion of the course. Rental education certificates shall be effective for six months
36 after the date of issuance and shall be valid anywhere in this state. Boat liveries may use
37 course materials either provided by or approved by the department. At a minimum, a
38 course must consist of a ten-minute operation familiarization video followed by a renter
39 orientation checklist. Such video must address the following topics in order to be
40 approved:
41 (A) Operator responsibility, ethics, courtesy, and good judgment on the water;
42 (B) Safety equipment;
43 (C) Navigation rules;
