44 (D) Aids to navigation, and buoys and other waterway markers; and
45 (E) Proper identification.
46 (4) The requirement to complete a course does not apply to any person licensed by the
47 United States Coast Guard as a master of a vessel, any person who has in his or her
48 possession a valid boater education identification card showing that he or she has
49 completed a boating education course approved by the department's Law Enforcement
50 Division, or a nonresident who has in his or her possession proof that he or she has
51 completed a National Association of State Boating Law Administrators approved boater
52 education course or equivalency examination from another state.
53 (5) Any person who violates this subsection shall be guilty of a misdemeanor."
54 SECTION 2.
55 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
